tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic expression in most cells at variable levels. Most abundant in the small intestine.

subcellularLocation.summary: Localized to the plasma membrane, vesicles or mitochondria.

tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic staining in most normal tissues. Luminal membrane immunoreactivity in intestinal glands, trophoblasts, bronchus and epididymis. Strong cytoplasmic staining in renal tubules, parathyroid gland and gastrointestinal glands. Distinct nuclear staining in Leydig cells and parathyroid glands.

Weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining in most malignancies. Distinct luminal membrane positivity was seen in colorectal carcinomas and weak nuclear staining in occasional cases of different cancer types. Lymphomas, melanomas, breast, skin, thyroid and testicular malignancies were mainly negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic staining in most tissues and cells, strong staining in gastrointestinal tract.

Weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining in several cases of colo-rectal, prostate, ovarial, endometrial, urothelial, renal, gastric, pancreatic and liver cancers. Breast, head and neck, thyroid, lymphomas, gliomas, melanomas skin and testis cancers were virtually negative.
